2. TOOLS REGISTRATION - HOW TO ADD TOOLS
================================================================================

TWO WAYS TO REGISTER TOOLS:

A) Via Constructor - Pass IList<AITool> tools parameter:
   var agent = new ChatClientAgent(
       chatClient,
       tools: new List<AITool> { tool1, tool2, ... }
   );

B) Via ChatClientAgentOptions - Set Tools property:
   var options = new ChatClientAgentOptions
   {
       // Tools are part of ChatOptions
   };

C) Via ChatOptions - Set Tools property:
   var chatOptions = new ChatOptions
   {
       Tools = new List<AITool> { tool1, tool2, ... }
   };

CREATING TOOLS:

AITool Constructor (requires name, description, function):
  new AITool(String name, String description, AIFunction function, IReadOnlyDictionary<String, Object> additionalProperties = null)

AIFunction Creation:
  AIFunction instances are created via AIFunctionFactory.Create():

  static AIFunction Create(Delegate method, AIFunctionFactoryOptions options)
  static AIFunction Create(Delegate method, String name, String description, JsonSerializerOptions serializerOptions)
  static AIFunction Create(MethodInfo method, Object target, AIFunctionFactoryOptions options)
  static AIFunction Create(MethodInfo method, Object target, String name, String description, JsonSerializerOptions serializerOptions)


